Original comment by: Robert Leftwich

This is great. 

I have a couple of suggestions for the `DirectionsView` (in the JavaScript part of the code). The two main issues are:

 - the implementation currently overwrites the model's data array when it extracts the last point and the waypoints. When you write `var data = this.model.get("data")`, this just copies a reference, not the array itself. The changes are not apparent until someone calls `this.touch()` on the view, which propagates the model changes back to Python. At that point, the Python layer tries to calculate bounds and everything breaks. 
 - raising an alert is probably not the best way to handle exceptions: it would be better to throw an exception in the Python layer. This is annoyingly tricky to do because the error happens in the front-end, and we need to somehow propagate it back to the Python kernel. There may be a simpler way to do this, but I suggest setting a flag called `layer_status` in the model and updating that flag from the view when the response comes in. The Python model can then observe that flag and raise an exception.

I've written a bit of code to illustrate those points:

```javascript
var DirectionsLayerView = GMapsLayerView.extend({
    render: function() {
        var that = this ;

        var rendererOptions = { map:this.map_view.map };

        that.directionsDisplay=new google.maps.DirectionsRenderer(rendererOptions);

        var model_data = this.model.get("data");
        var orig = that.get_orig(model_data);
        var dest = that.get_dest(model_data);
        var waypoints = that.get_wps(model_data);

        var request= {
            origin: orig,
            destination: dest,
            waypoints: waypoints,
            travelMode: google.maps.DirectionsTravelMode.DRIVING
        };

        var direction_service = new google.maps.DirectionsService();

        direction_service.route(request, function(response,status) {
           // print to the browser console (mostly for debugging) 
           console.log("Directon service returned: ", status) ; 
           // set a flag in the model
            that.model.set("layer_status", status) ; 
            that.touch() ; // push `layer_status` changes to the model
            if (status == google.maps.DirectionsStatus.OK) {
                that.response = that.directionsDisplay
                that.directionsDisplay.setDirections(response);
            }
        });
    },


    add_to_map_view: function(map_view) {},

    get_orig: function(model_data) {
        var first_point = _.first(model_data);
        return new google.maps.LatLng(first_point[0], first_point[1]);
    },

    get_dest: function(model_data) {
        var last_point = _.last(model_data); 
        return new google.maps.LatLng(last_point[0], last_point[1]);
    },

    get_wps: function(model_data) {
        var without_first = _.tail(model_data);
        var without_last = _.initial(without_first) ;
        var data_as_google = _.map(without_last, function(point) {
            var google_point = new google.maps.LatLng(point[0], point[1]);
            return google_point;
        });
        return data_as_google;
    }

});
```

