Currently, we are opening supplied index file in `a+` mode so that we first read any contents if the file exists (a file with that name will be created if not already). We populate cdxjLines array with the line we read from the existing file so that it is merged with the new stuff that is yet to be indexed. We keep the handle of that open file until it is time to write the merged content to it. We then truncate the index file and write merged index lines to it.

An alternate approach would be to open the file in read mode first (if any) then close it and populate the array. Later, open the file in write mode just before writing.

