I agree that OpenThread should be compatible with as many toolchains as possible.  Abstracting out the `packed` attribute is certainly useful.  However, `toolchain.h` goes far beyond what is needed for interfacing with the OpenThread library - the only attribute OpenThread relies on is `packed`.  Projects including OpenThread should not be bothered with worrying about all other macros that have no dependency.  If we only add the `packed` macros, then I think it is sufficient to add to `openthread-types.h`.

Specifically on `packed`, what about defining a single macro that supports both pre-pended, post-pended, and even inserted decorations?

```c++
#define PACK(decl) decl __attribute__((packed))

PACK(struct foo
{
    ...
});
```

